  <title>Dialog: Ball-Joint</title>
  <keywords>
    <keyword>Ball-Joint dialog-box</keyword>
    <keyword>Ball-Joint: Diameter</keyword>
    <keyword>Ball-Joint: Effective Mass</keyword>
    <keyword>Ball-Joint: Offset from Mechanism Plane</keyword>
    <keyword>Dialog<keyword>Ball-Joint</keyword></keyword>
    <keyword>How to edit a Ball-Joint:<keyword>Effective Mass</keyword><keyword>Offset from Mechanism Plane</keyword><keyword>Radius</keyword></keyword>
  </keywords>
  <body>
    <header>
      <para styleclass="Heading1">Dialog: Ball-Joint</para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Heading2">Ball-Joint</para>
    <para styleclass="SeeAlso">See: <link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-Mechanism-Ball-Joint">Add Ball-Joint</link>. Tutorial 12: Design a Spatial Mechanism</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><line style="height:1px; color:#993300;" /></para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo">We use the <text styleclass="Element">Ball-Joint</text> for spatial mechanisms. </para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo">Most often, <text styleclass="Element">Ball-Joints</text> join <text styleclass="Element">Parts</text> that are in different <text styleclass="Interface">Mechanism-Editors</text><text styleclass="Body Text">, such that their </text><text styleclass="Interface">Mechanism-Planes</text> are perpendicular(<text style="font-family:Tahoma;">⊥</text>).</para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><text styleclass="Body Text">A </text><text styleclass="Element">Ball-Joint</text><text styleclass="Body Text"> must be added to each end of one </text><text styleclass="Element">Part</text><text styleclass="Body Text">. &#160;</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><text styleclass="Body Text">The derived name for the </text><text styleclass="Element">Part</text><text styleclass="Body Text"> is the </text><text styleclass="Interface">Connecting-Part.</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><line style="height:1px; color:#993300;" /></para>
    <para styleclass="Heading3_atocs_">Open the Ball-Joint dialog-box</para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><table styleclass="Standard" rowcount="2" colcount="2">
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td style="width:160px;">
          <para styleclass="Normal" style="text-align:right;"><image src="GA-Click-BallJoint.png" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Image Caption"></image></para>
        </td>
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Body Text">The <text styleclass="Element">Ball-Joint </text>element may be <text styleclass="VariableName-IT">inside</text> the symbol of the <link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-Connecting-Part" styleclass="Element">Connecting-Part</link>.</para>
          <list id="25" type="ol" listtype="decimal" formatstring="&#37;&#48;&#58;&#115;&#46;" format-charset="DEFAULT_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="HowTo Numbered" style="font-family:&apos;Segoe UI Semibold&apos;; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; color:#000000;">
            <li styleclass="HowTo Numbered">Move your pointer above the end of the <text styleclass="Interface">Connecting-Part</text> until the <text styleclass="Element">Ball-Joint</text> is <text styleclass="VariableName-IT" style="color:#ff0000;">red</text> - see image<text styleclass="VariableName">. </text></li>
            <li styleclass="HowTo Numbered"><text style="font-style:normal;">Click</text> the symbol for the <text styleclass="Element">Ball-Joint</text><image src="Red-14-1.gif" scale="100.00%"></image>. </li>
          </list>
        </td>
      </tr>
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td style="width:160px;">
          <para styleclass="Normal"><image src="SW-BallJoint-Edit.png" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Image Caption"><title>Ball-Joint in the Selection-Window</title><caption><![CDATA[Ball-Joint in the Selection-Window]]></caption></image></para>
        </td>
        <td>
          <para styleclass="HowTo Numbered">The <text styleclass="Element">Ball-Joint</text> element should be in the <link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-Selection-Window" styleclass="Interface">Selection-Window</link><text style="font-weight:bold;">&#32;</text></para>
          <list id="26" type="ol" listtype="decimal" formatstring="&#37;&#48;&#58;&#115;&#46;" format-charset="DEFAULT_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="3" styleclass="HowTo Numbered" style="font-family:&apos;Segoe UI Semibold&apos;; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; color:#000000;">
            <li styleclass="HowTo Numbered"><text style="font-style:normal;">Right-click</text> the <text styleclass="Element">Ball-Joint</text> in the <text styleclass="Interface">Selection-Window</text><text styleclass="VariableName">&#32;</text></li>
            <li styleclass="HowTo Numbered"><text style="font-style:normal;">Click</text>&#32;<text styleclass="VariableName">Edit Element </text>in the contextual-menu.</li>
          </list>
          <para styleclass="Body Text">The <text styleclass="Element">Ball-Joint dialog-box</text> is now open.</para>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><line style="height:1px; color:#993300;" /></para>
    <para styleclass="Heading3_atocs_">Ball-Joint dialog-box</para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo">Usually, you would edit the <text styleclass="Interface">Ball-Joint</text> at each end of the <link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-Connecting-Part" styleclass="Interface">Connecting-Part</link>.</para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><table styleclass="Standard" rowcount="2" colcount="2">
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td style="width:160px;">
          <para styleclass="Normal" style="text-align:right;"><image src="Dialog-13.2-BallJoint.ipp" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Image Caption"></image></para>
        </td>
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Parameter-Header">Ball Diameter</para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo">Edit the diameter of the Ball symbol in <text styleclass="Interface">graphic-area.</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text"><text styleclass="Notes">Note: &#160;</text><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo">Do </text><text styleclass="T_Menu">Visibility toolbar &gt; </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-Visibility-Show-Model-in-Mechanism" styleclass="T_Menu">Show Model in Mechanism</link><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo"> to view the symbol for the Ball. </text></para>
          <para styleclass="Normal"><line style="height:1px; color:#993300;" /></para>
          <para styleclass="Parameter-Header">Ball Offset &#160;<text styleclass="BodyText BI">(±)</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo">Edit the perpendicular distance <text styleclass="BodyText BI">(±)</text> from the <link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-Plane-Mechanism" styleclass="Element">Mechanism Plane</link> to the center of the <text styleclass="Element">Ball-Joint.</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Normal"><line style="height:1px; color:#993300;" /></para>
          <para styleclass="VariableName">Why do you need the <text styleclass="Parameter-Header">Ball-Offset</text> parameter?</para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text - bit bit bigger2"><text styleclass="Body Text">Unlike other kinematic-elements, the center of </text><text styleclass="Element">Ball-Joints</text><text styleclass="Body Text"> are frequently </text><text styleclass="VariableName-IT" style="color:#ff0000;">not</text><text styleclass="Body Text"> on the </text><text styleclass="Interface">Mechanism-Plane. </text><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo">It is important that the offset distance to the center of the </text><text styleclass="Element">Ball-Joint</text><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo"> is correct to make sure the kinematic-analysis is correct.</text></para>
          <para styleclass="SeeAlso">See also : <link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-Ball-Joint-Configurations">Ball-Joint Configurations</link></para>
          <para styleclass="Normal"><line style="height:1px; color:#993300;" /></para>
          <para styleclass="Parameter-Header">Ball Mass</para>
          <para styleclass="HowTo Numbered"><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo">Enter the Mass of the </text><text styleclass="Element">Ball-Joint</text><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo">.</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo">Its center-of-mass is coplanar with the <text styleclass="Interface">Mechanism-Plane</text>. even if the <text styleclass="Parameter">Ball-Offset ≠ 0 </text>.</para>
        </td>
      </tr>
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td style="width:160px;">
          <para styleclass="Normal" style="text-align:right;"><image src="GA-BallJoint-Offset.png" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Image Caption"></image></para>
        </td>
        <td>
          <para styleclass="VariableName">Example of Ball-Offset : Z = 10<text style="font-size:10pt; vertical-align:baseline;">mm</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text">This image shows model from the &#160;left - <text styleclass="T_Menu">View toolbar &gt; Left-View</text>&#32;<text styleclass="VariableName">(Shortcut : F7).</text></para>
          <para styleclass="HowTo Bulleted"><image src="Red-14-1b.gif" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Image Caption"></image>&#32;<text styleclass="Interface">Mechanism-Plane</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo">The <text styleclass="Element">Ball-Joint</text> is on the <text styleclass="Interface">Mechanism-Plane</text> when the <text styleclass="Parameter">Ball-Offset</text> = 0<text style="font-size:10pt; vertical-align:baseline;">mm</text>.</para>
          <para styleclass="HowTo Bulleted"><image src="Red-14-2.gif" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Image Caption"></image>&#32;<text styleclass="Parameter">Ball-Offset</text>.</para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo">The <text styleclass="Element">Ball-Joint</text> can move in the <text styleclass="Interface">+Z-axis</text> or <text styleclass="Interface">–Z-axis</text> direction.</para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo">In the image, the <text styleclass="Parameter">Ball-Offset</text> = <text styleclass="VariableName">10</text><text styleclass="VariableName" style="font-size:10pt; vertical-align:baseline;">mm</text><text styleclass="Body Text"> in the +Z-axis direction</text>.</para>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table></para>
  </body>
